## 
##   - KMO: The Kaiser, Meyer, Olkin (KMO) measure of sampling adequacy suggests that data seems appropriate for factor analysis (KMO = 0.93).
##   - Sphericity: Bartlett's test of sphericity suggests that there is sufficient significant correlation in the data for factor analaysis (Chisq(36) = 4060.92, p < .001).
